WEBVTT

00:00.913 --> 00:02.182
Previously on The Resident...

00:05.841 --> 00:07.409
We can all agree

00:07.443 --> 00:10.546
- it was the misdosed sevo.
- That's never gonna fly.

00:10.579 --> 00:12.147
I covered for you.
Not this time.

00:12.180 --> 00:14.583
We cannot handle
one more lawsuit.

00:14.616 --> 00:15.817
I have installed
recording devices

00:15.851 --> 00:17.919
on every camera in every OR.

00:17.953 --> 00:19.154
Doctors must support each other

00:19.187 --> 00:21.490
through good times and bad.

00:21.523 --> 00:23.225
Time of death, 21:58

00:23.259 --> 00:24.693
I don't understand.

00:24.726 --> 00:27.162
She was stable last night
when I left my shift.

00:27.195 --> 00:30.366
I went home, I left her alone.

00:30.399 --> 00:31.967
I should have stayed here.

00:34.202 --> 00:37.172
Healing hands
and the spirit of care.

00:37.205 --> 00:39.375
Chastain Memorial Hospital.

00:39.408 --> 00:42.244
Incredible things
are happening here.

00:42.278 --> 00:44.045
You got to be kidding me.

00:44.079 --> 00:45.581
Incredible things?

00:45.614 --> 00:46.715
Wow.

00:47.749 --> 00:49.285
Hey.

00:49.318 --> 00:51.520
Mina told me to find you.

00:51.553 --> 00:54.022
Dr. Bell just started the lipoma
excision on your patient.

00:54.055 --> 00:56.258
- Turner was scheduled for that.
- Yeah.

00:56.292 --> 00:57.459
He's out sick. Stomach flu.

00:57.493 --> 00:58.794
Wait, that's TJ's surgery.

00:58.827 --> 01:00.429
Doesn't he have
a latex sensitivity?

01:00.462 --> 01:02.464
You're right. I need
to check on him, and Bell.

01:02.498 --> 01:05.266
Hey.

01:05.301 --> 01:06.368
Go easy on your ankle today.

01:06.402 --> 01:08.036
What ankle?

01:08.069 --> 01:09.070
the spirit of care.

01:09.104 --> 01:11.273
Chastain Memorial Hospital.

01:11.307 --> 01:14.242
Incredible things
are happening here.

01:14.276 --> 01:15.477
Pickups.

01:17.513 --> 01:19.481
- Give him five, imidazoline.
- Anyone seen

01:19.515 --> 01:20.482
the new hospital promo?

01:20.516 --> 01:22.117
Oh, I saw it.

01:22.150 --> 01:23.985
You're fantastic, Dr. Bell.

01:24.019 --> 01:26.388
What about you, Dr. Okafor?

01:26.422 --> 01:28.590
You're in it.

01:34.162 --> 01:36.264
Silk.

01:40.969 --> 01:42.103
How much longer?

01:42.137 --> 01:43.472
Just have to close up.

01:43.505 --> 01:45.674
Some bleeding posteriorly.

01:45.707 --> 01:47.142
Yeah, I got it.

01:47.175 --> 01:48.777
Cautery.

01:48.810 --> 01:52.314
Set to 40:40 blend point.

01:52.348 --> 01:53.549
Mm-hmm.

01:56.284 --> 01:58.587
Damn it.

01:58.620 --> 02:00.922
Shut off the oxygen.
Look, I got to keep sterile

02:00.956 --> 02:03.258
so I can close the patient.
Get the O2 off!

02:05.060 --> 02:08.830
- Get that O2 mask off.
- Rip the drapes down.

02:08.864 --> 02:11.467
More oxygen might be
hiding beneath them.

02:14.536 --> 02:16.237
Hey, Mina, I need you sterile.

02:17.973 --> 02:19.641
Paul. Paul,
I need you to bag him.

02:23.579 --> 02:25.347
It's still open.
I got to cover the incision.

02:25.381 --> 02:27.215
Can't let him get hypothermic.

02:27.248 --> 02:30.018
Someone get those sprinklers
turned off!

02:30.051 --> 02:33.188
Incredible things
are happening here.

